    "aboutTitle": "About \"Tree of Knowledge\"",
    "aboutDesc1": "The Tree of Knowledge is a platform that organizes knowledge into a tree diagram through consultation and collaboration among researchers. This diagram is not limited to nodes and lines; each node has a data card containing scientific content and even links to detailed articles.",
    "aboutDesc2": "This diagram and the grand map of knowledge are in constant evolution thanks to the consultation of researchers, and better and more complete versions are issued continuously. Contributors to this project are divided into two categories: Editors who only submit their proposals and can defend them in the comments or express their opinions on the proposals of others. The second category is Supervisors, a scientific elite characterized by depth, insight, and commitment to the teachings of the Yamani (pbuh) call. This group, through a voting process after discussion and dialogue, approves the appropriate proposals.",
    "whyImportantTitle": "Why is \"Tree of Knowledge\" important?",
    "whyImportantDesc1": "In a world where we face a data explosion, nothing is more important than reliability, accuracy, and depth. We seek in this platform for the evolution of knowledge to be supervised by a scientific elite with depth, insight, and commitment to the teachings of the Yamani (pbuh) call, and this will be one of the most prominent advantages of the platform.",
    "whyImportantDesc2": "Also, the basis of this tree encyclopedia is to organize and arrange scientific concepts and materials so that each concept and article has its correct place within the system.",
    "structureTitle": "Structure",
    "structureItem1": "Everyone can participate in this project by registering as an editor.",
    "structureItem2": "On the new edit page, you can delete or add nodes, or delete/add/edit cards. You can also link articles to cards or edit existing articles.",
    "structureItem3": "If you feel there is a conceptual relationship between nodes, you can add related nodes in the \"Related to\" section at the end of the card.",
    "structureItem4": "Proposals receive a decimal identifier and are sent to the experts' panel.",
    "structureItem5": "Finally, the experts review the proposals in their panel, and after visual comparison and discussion in the comments, they give them a rating.",
    "structureItem6": "If the ratings reach a quorum, i.e., half the number of experts, and at least half of them participate in the vote, the plan is published and receives a new identifier.",
    "structureItem7": "If several edits are made to one version and the publishing conditions are met for two or more, the first proposal that gained the votes is published and the rest are marked with a \"Reviewable\" tag. Then editors are asked to re-apply their ideas to the new published version and resubmit.",
    "structureItem8": "This platform is in constant development, and with God's help, more features will be added to it.",
    "footerQuote": "So give good tidings to My servants who listen to speech and follow the best of it. Those are the ones Allah has guided, and those are people of understanding. (Az-Zumar: 17, 18)"
  },
